<paragraph id="5D0336F9FFED9A36F87C1687F9DFF393" blockId="5.[2072,2658,2575,3001]" lastBlockId="5.[1456,2659,3007,3473]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">Pocock revised this genus and recognized two species occurring in the eastern humid forest: G. eximius in the north and G. ornatus in the south. Subsequently, Albignac reduced these to one species and recognized G. eximius as G. f. fasciatus and G. ornatus as G. [. strata. These two geographic forms are recognized here, but are poorly differentiated, and based on current evidence probably do not warrant recognition.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
